## Task 3 — Mysterious Landmark

### Technique: Image Geolocation (GeoINT)

The image shows a tall, thin steel monument located in the center of a busy street, with a historic building in the background.

**Visual clues:**
- European architecture
- Spire/needle-shaped monument
- Historic building on the right with a role in national independence

The monument is the **Spire of Dublin** (The Needle), located on **O'Connell Street**, Dublin, Ireland. The building beside it is the **General Post Office (GPO)** — headquarters of the 1916 Easter Rising, a central landmark in Ireland's fight for independence.

**Flag:** `THM{General Post Office}`

