## Task 4 — Internal Documents

### Technique: Metadata Analysis in ODT Documents

`.odt` files (LibreOffice) are actually ZIP archives containing multiple XMLs. Document metadata is stored in `meta.xml`.

Extracting the contents:

```bash
unzip internal-docs.odt -d internal-docs/
cat internal-docs/meta.xml
```

**Relevant output:**
```xml
<dc:description>Just remember Robin, don't publish this externally!</dc:description>
<meta:user-defined meta:name="Internal username">markwilliams7243</meta:user-defined>
```

Using the username `markwilliams7243`, searching across public platforms (YouTube, social media) led to a post containing the final flag.

**Flag:** `THM{Y0u_f0und_7h3_fin4l_fl4g!}`

